Harrison User stories:

View User Detials Story
-As a user, I want to view a selected person’s profile details so that I can understand who they are and see their personal information in one place.
Details:

The application retrieves user data from /user/:id
The page displays the user’s:
First name
Last name
Location
Description
Occupation
Information is presented in a clear, readable layout

Navigate to User Photos Story
-As a user, I want to navigate from a person’s profile to their photo collection so that I can continue exploring related content without searching manually.

Details:

The user detail page includes a button or link to view photos
Clicking the control navigates to /photos/:userId
The correct user ID is preserved in the route


Dynamic TopBar Story
-As a user, I want the TopBar to display the name of the user whose profile I am viewing so that I always know whose information I am looking at.
Details:

The TopBar updates dynamically based on the selected user
The user’s name appears on the right side of the TopBar
The team name remains on the left side



William Brodersen User Stories:

1. As a user, I want to see all photos uploaded by a user so I am better able to explore their content
- [] All photos for the selected user are displayed
- [] Each photo shows: Image & upload date/time

2. As a user, I want to read comments on each photo, so that I am able to see interactions with that photo and potentially interact with it myself
- [] Each photo displays all associated comments
- [] Each comment shows:
     Comment text
     Date/time
     Comment author name
3. As a user, I want to click on a comment author's name, so that I can view their profile and interact with their other photos if I choose to
- [] Author's name is clickable
- [] Navigates to /users/:userId
- [] Correct user details load
